{
  "texts": [
    "Their research leverages ML to learn the processor's timing model and integrates it with static analysis to estimate WCETs.",
    "The approach operates on binary code to improve precision and uses a large set of automatically generated basic blocks for training.",
    "By incorporating cache modeling, WE-HML improves the accuracy of WCET estimates compared to cache-agnostic techniques.",
    "Experiments conducted on an ARM Cortex-A53 processor demonstrate that WE-HML consistently produces WCET estimates higher than the maximum observed execution times, highlighting its effectiveness and reliability.",
    "Shah et al. [99] investigate using GAs to estimate WCET in real-time systems, proposing predictive models to replace simulator-based evaluations."
  ]
}